&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Fellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fellow, we’re on a mission to help people brew ridiculously good coffee at home. But we’re more than just beautifully designed kettles and grinders—we’re a brand built on innovation, community, and culture. We believe great coffee isn’t just about the final cup; it’s about the experience, the ritual, and the people who make it all happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Product Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to focus on and own our brewing category through future accessories and platform extensions. You’ll act as the “mini-CEO” of the category, owning the product vision, roadmap, and commercial outcomes across DTC, retail, and global markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is based in our San Francisco, CA office and requires regular in-office presence in accordance with company policy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You thrive in highly cross-functional environments, operating at the intersection of coffee excellence, engineering, design, and business. You have translated customer insights and market trends into a clear product strategy, and you’re comfortable making courageous tradeoffs between cost, features, and timelines. You excel at driving alignment from early concept through launch and post-launch optimization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior individual contributor,&amp;nbsp; you’re confident in influencing decisions at the highest levels of the organization. You’re comfortable presenting to executives and board members, and you have collaborated with leaders across Product Engineering, R&amp;amp;D, Marketing, and Commercial teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Vision &amp;amp; Strategy - Brewing&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end product vision and long-term roadmap for Fellow’s brewing platform (machines, accessories, and ecosystem features).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define what “Fellow-level brewing” means across performance, reliability, experience, and aesthetics—and translate that into clear product requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a deep understanding of the brewing landscape (home and prosumer), competitive set, and emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer &amp;amp; Market Insight&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive qualitative and quantitative research with home baristas, prosumers, cafes, and partners to uncover needs, pain points, and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize insights into clear problem statements and prioritized opportunities, balancing enthusiast feature asks with broad-market needs and price sensitivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roadmap, Requirements &amp;amp; Tradeoffs&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
