&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Fellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that the act of making should be meaningful and fulfilling, done with intention and precision. Fellow makes beautifully functional tools for any kitchen, designed in San Francisco and used around the world. When the simple motions of life become small moments of joy, that&#39;s Everyday Magic.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;VP of Manufacturing &amp;amp; Quality&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;that is central to Fellow&#39;s success, leading and optimizing all key quality and sustaining functions. This includes Quality Management, Manufacturing Test, Sustaining Engineering, Supplier Quality, and Compliance Support. This role demands a strategic and hands-on leader who can develop and execute quality strategies that support Fellow&#39;s rapid growth and commitment to delivering exceptional customer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on leadership position where you will build and lead quality teams in the US and China. This position requires flexible scheduling, with overlap during U.S. Pacific business hours and occasional evening collaboration with Asia-based teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports to the Chief Product and Technology Officer (CPTO).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is based in our San Francisco, CA office and requires regular in-office presence in accordance with company policy. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership and Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;: Develop and execute a cohesive quality vision and strategy that aligns with Fellow&#39;s business objectives. Build and lead a high-performing team, fostering a culture of collaboration, continuous improvement, and data-driven decision-making. Champion quality excellence across the organization, focusing on efficiency, scalability, product reliability, and customer satisfaction. Wake up every day thinking about how to make our existing products better.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Management&lt;/strong&gt;: Define quality metrics and drive the data analytics team to establish and maintain effective dashboards for monitoring performance. Implement and maintain a robust quality management system (QMS) to ensure all products meet Fellow&#39;s premium standards. Set up long-term reporting metrics from suppliers and oversee quality control processes throughout the supply chain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sustaining Engineering&lt;/strong&gt;: Prioritize fixes for organizational resolution and direct sustaining engineers to solve ongoing problems. Guide failure analysis of field issues and handle firefighting for urgent sustaining challenges. Focus on continuous improvement of our product lines to address constant sustaining issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supplier and Manufacturer Quality&lt;/strong&gt;: Push manufacturers and suppliers to improve their testing, quality coverage, and manufacturing processes. Hold suppliers accountable to key quality metrics, driving proper reporting and feedback.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manufacturing Engineering &amp;amp; Test: &lt;/strong&gt;Own our end of line testing to ensure proper coverage of devices to uphold our strongest quality standards. Work closely with the engineering team to identify potential failure points and instill a robust test process to mitigate issues.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance Support&lt;/strong&gt;: Support compliance efforts, initially through the development and maintenance of regulatory dashboards, ensuring adherence to relevant standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
