&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Fellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that the act of making should be meaningful and fulfilling, done with intention and precision. Fellow makes beautifully functional tools for any kitchen, designed in San Francisco and used around the world. When the simple motions of life become small moments of joy, that&#39;s Everyday Magic.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;VP of Software&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to own the entire software ecosystem—spanning Embedded Firmware, Control Systems, Mobile Apps, and Cloud Backend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission is to build the &quot;machine that builds the machine.&quot; We are looking for a systems thinker obsessed with operational leverage–someone who ensures that as our product line expands from kettles and grinders to complex brewing ecosystems, our engineering velocity accelerates, and system reliability improves at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is based in our San Francisco, CA office and requires regular in-office presence in accordance with company policy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re an experienced engineering leader who has built and led multidisciplinary teams across software, hardware, product, and design. You know how to align functions around a shared roadmap, make clear tradeoffs, and create accountability without friction. As products grow more complex, you understand how to structure teams, processes, and architecture to scale. You foster a culture of ownership, close collaboration, and open communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You care deeply about how software is built. You’ve implemented automated CI/CD pipelines and strong testing practices that support complex products, reducing manual work and improving reliability. You use metrics to understand delivery performance and team health, pairing data with sound judgment. You’re pragmatic, curious, and motivated to build products that are both technically rigorous and thoughtfully designed. You’re motivated by raising the bar, not maintaining the status quo.&lt;/p&gt;
